item.comment: This game was a whimsical purchase. We played it and L won. I like the game and give them props for their beautiful packaging. Unfortunately, I just don't think it's particularly unique. You'd think it would be unique with the transparent layering of cards, and on the face it appears to be unique, but the way it's executed is so similar in style and feel to Cascadia and other tile selection and laying games that it just doesn't feel fresh or new. I'd play it again with a glass of whisky (this is a whiskey game), but I think my first choice for this style would be Cascadia.
